@@eThe Eccentric Woodland -- Ledger House Marginal Assessment@@N

The @@yLedger Houses@@N file the Eccentric Woodland under @@dNon-
Contributing Territory, No Attestation Required@@N. It produces
nothing that reaches our docks in identifiable volume. It controls
no route we depend on. By every metric the Sand-Sea Carters' Guild
uses to prioritize intelligence, it is @@yirrelevant@@N.

And yet the Ledger Clerks keep the file, because what the Woodland
demonstrates is instructive.

@@yMidgaard@@N -- the continent's self-proclaimed center of stone law
-- cannot govern a forest @@rimmediately south of its own gates@@N.
Patrol reports from every era note the same failures: path drift,
contradictory witness accounts, landmarks that vanish on follow-up.
The city's response is always bureaucratic: keep the gate records
clean, classify incidents as variance events, maintain plausible
governance at the edge.

Our Harbor Wardens have a term for this: @@rpaper jurisdiction@@N.
The map says Midgaard governs. The ground says otherwise. In Mafdet,
the Dual-Attestation Protocol exists because a document claiming
authority is worthless unless someone physically verifies the claim.
@@dA manifest without inspection is decoration.@@N

The Woodland's four competing forces -- @@gPath Wardens@@N selling
navigation, @@dRitual Houses@@N legitimating rank through ceremony,
@@rPredator Bands@@N mimicking ritual for extraction, @@ySurvivor
Clusters@@N bartering in clearings -- describe a zone where attestation
has collapsed. No one verifies anyone else's claims. Authority is
local, theatrical, and temporary. This is the condition the
Strandline Compact prevents in our own harbor.

If the Woodland exported anything of value, it would arrive at our
docks with no chain of custody, no recognized seals, and no
attestation authority behind the manifest. The Quarantine Ledger
would flag every item.

The lesson for Mafdet: @@ygovernance that stops at the wall is not
governance@@N. Our Harbor Wardens patrol beyond the harbor chain. Our
Reach Wardens walk the cairn lines. Our Carters carry Guild seals
into the deep desert. @@gJurisdiction must reach as far as the goods
travel@@N, or it means nothing.

The Eccentric Woodland does not threaten us. It @@rteaches@@N us -- by
example of what we must never become: a port that controls its quays
but not its approaches.
